{
  "stem": "17821.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 95.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So Martin came on that ship and he was in a cabin with several French officers who were coming to this country to be on the Normandy that was in New York City, in the harbor.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I'm losing my thread.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That ship, he joined you in Martinique.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, so we got to Martinique.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Before we arrived in the Martinique, we were boarded by French officers who took away any money we had with us and separated the men from the women.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then when we arrived, we were sent to different camps.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At the, at the first day, they put us through the examining as though we were regular travelers-- customs, we were examined at customs.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I had a pile of folders, I brought a lot of papers with me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The things that I brought from France for, for Metro-Goldwyn.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so they-- I got a man and he would take one folder up and open it and look through it and close it and put it on one side.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he would be constantly taking a folder up and put it down on the other pile.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "At one point, he was called away for something.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And while he was gone, I thought to myself, do I, do I or don't I, because I could see that the next folder had information in it about the horse farm that they, that the Germans had seized.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so I just quickly took that and turned it over.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And also, I knew the name of the Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer-- the man in the Metro-- Martinique man who did business with Metro-Goldwyn.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I said to Martin, just go quickly and find a telephone and telephone to him, which he did.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But he didn't get him.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
